    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix unreachable code path in M3AP MCE SCTP initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe M3AP MCE module contained unreachable error handling code due to incorrect conditional logic in the SCTP initialization flow. The bug manifested when memory allocation failed during SCTP message creation, causing a segmentation fault instead of proper error handling.\n\nThe unreachable code was in `m3ap_MCE_handle_register_MCE` function where the error handling block (lines 375-376) could never be executed because `m3ap_MCE_init_sctp` always returned 0 regardless of allocation success.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE.c`: Added NULL check for `itti_alloc_new_message` in `m3ap_MCE_init_sctp` and return -1 on failure to make error handling reachable\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE.c`: Added NULL check in `m3ap_MCE_register_MCE` to prevent potential crashes\n\n"
}